      "text": "Buying the right resistor is not only about choosing the right ohms — you also need a part that can shed the heat it will dissipate without burning out. Wattage rating is the second number on every resistor's datasheet, and it matters as soon as the calculation in the previous section gives you anything above a fraction of a watt."
