      "text": " Set the multimeter to DC volts (2 V range or autorange). Touch the probes across the AA cell — you should read somewhere around 1.5 V. Now switch the meter to AC volts and probe the same cell. The reading should collapse to near zero (at most a few millivolts of meter noise). A DC source has no alternating component."
