      "text": " Plug your USB charger in. Find its +5 V and GND pins (or use a USB breakout). Measure on DC — about 5 V. Switch to AC — should again read near zero, because the charger's internal filter capacitors have smoothed its output. If you do read a millivolt or two of AC, that is "
