     "text": "A multimeter's DC mode averages; its AC mode measures what is left after blocking the DC average (internally via a capacitor). DC + AC together describe the whole waveform. This is the same decomposition every oscilloscope, every spectrum analyser, and every radio front end relies on — and the reason cheap multimeters give misleading numbers on PWM: they assume whatever they are measuring is a sine."
