      "text": ". It should sag by a small but visible amount (roughly 3 %). Replace the 100 kΩ with the 10 kΩ; re-measure. Now the sag is large — the rule of thumb «keep the load at least ten times the divider's parallel resistance» is being violated. Replace with the 1 kΩ load and see the divider collapse."
