     "text": "This lab links the static facts of the colour code to the behaviour of resistors inside a working circuit. The divider you built is one of the most common circuits in electronics — the same topology drives sensor readouts, microcontroller reference voltages, and the first stage of oscilloscope probes. The loading experiment is your first encounter with the fact that circuits interact when you connect them, which motivates the Thévenin-equivalent discussion in Chapter 1.7."
