      "text": " Add the 1 MΩ resistor across the parallel LC. Sweep again. The resonant frequency should be essentially unchanged, but the peak should be lower and broader — Q has dropped because the resistor is dissipating energy each cycle. Repeat the bandwidth measurement and verify Q has fallen. Replace the 1 MΩ with progressively smaller values (100 kΩ, 10 kΩ) and watch Q collapse. This is exactly how a load coupled to a tank in a real radio reduces the loaded Q."
